</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[264,1323,1073,1339]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,443,1073,1099]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Identification:</emphasis>
Forewing length 15.0–17.0 mm. All the species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1821" box="[1042,1117,1073,1098]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Euxoa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1042,1117,1073,1098]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Euxoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
treated here have a round unscaled frontal tubercle on the frons and biserrate male antennae. Forewing ground color is gray. The forewing lines, antemedial, median, postmedial, and subterminal are faint, slightly darker than the ground color, and extend from costa to posterior margin. Reniform spot is represented by a faint, small round dot at end of discal cell. Hindwing is white in the male and dark gray in the female.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[264,1323,1073,1339]" box="[312,798,1313,1339]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,485,1313,1339]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Flight period:</emphasis>
